{"questionId":"13719200","questionHtml":"<p>Hence, perform the test to a <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo> </mo><mo>%</mo></math> significance level, clearly stating the conclusion in context.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>d</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">f</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(A1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo> </mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0166</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0166282</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p>comparing their <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math>-value to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>05</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>R1</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0166</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>05</mn></math></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Accept <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math> value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0165</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0164693</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;from using <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi></math> to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn></math> sf.</p>\n<p>(Reject&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math>, There is sufficient evidence to say that) the data has not&nbsp;been drawn from the&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>176</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>13</mn><mo>.</mo><msup><mn>5</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;distribution.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Do not award <em><strong>R0A1</strong></em>.</p>\n<p>The conclusion to part (e)(ii) <strong>MUST</strong> follow through from their hypotheses seen in part (d); if hypotheses are incorrect/reversed etc., the answer to part (e)(ii) must reflect this in order for the <em><strong>A1</strong> </em>to be credited.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13719200","referenceCode":"23N.2.SL.TZ2.3eii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Hence, perform the test to a 5 % significance level, clearly stating the conclusion in context.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.9—Normal distribution and calculations","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.11—Expected, observed, hypotheses, chi squared, gof, t-test"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}